<item>
            <title>[HBASE-16273] Display ServerLoad sizes in appropriate units</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-16273</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently store file size is reported in MB and index &amp;amp; bloom filter in kb.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are two problems here.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) They are calculated from bytes by dividing by 1024 / 1024 and then converted to an int. So for small regions it always reports 0. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) And this conversion is done per store so even if there are multiple stores and all of them combined would be larger than 1 MB it&apos;d be reported as 0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d suggest to count them in bytes and then when displaying them on the RegionServer UI page decide on an appropriate unit to use.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
